<font color="#FF0000">MEETING OF MINDS 'N NOT</font><br>
<tt>Mon Apr 21  2:13:46 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doc Barry Spatz - Hornets nest, Barry? It has been a while since we could discuss some subject of substance instead of bemoaning the demise of this site. This is what it is all about and I also thank you, Barry.  You say we went off on a tangent. From my perspective, the issues that came forth were not frivilous nor a waste of cyberspace. To an certain extent, there has been a meeting of the minds, at the very least, a clearing of each others position on important matters. In other words we used our damn grey matter, and not just reacted from the gut.  I saw this in your writings. I tried to put this in mine. You were not dismissive of my positions, as I also, saw that in your writings. Even if you disagreed with my positions, it was evident that you reflected on what I had to say. At this point, we have reached a junction where all we would end up doing would be rehashing what we have already said with very little more to gain.   <br><br>
It is suprising that you were suprised by Lien's reaction to your posts as aren't you the master, no, the supreme master of taking the jabs that have so endeared us to you? Let me take you down memory lane to, oh, let's say, about post 40 through about 200 of the &quot;protestors&quot; thread. I doubt that there was not one of us vets who didn't have a fantasy of giving you a special necktie, at one time or another, if you know what I mean. Or, how about when you decided to take issues with the veterans medals. I know I heard many 16's lock 'n load all the way over here in Hawaii. It's a very distinctive sound, let me tell ya. Never thought you would survive that one. So why is it that it seemed you were ambushed by a college student's reaction who is at least half the age of us hard core, combat seasoned vets, HUH? <br><br>
&quot;However, when I knock multi-culturalism as dangerous to our country, it is because I see it pulling that salad bowl apart, and we become a bunch of veggies back in the produce section, with no bond holding us together. That mostly is, to me,in the need to hang extra I.D.'s, like Blank-American when describing one's self or another group.&quot;<br><br>
I like the salad analogy better, also, as it is more apt. Where you and I will continue to disagree is the fact that we are all Americans and always will be and when the need arises we will all &quot;pull together&quot;. This is how it always has been and nothing is changed by the fact that some groups of people want to call themselves ______________-Americans. As with Mr. Fujihara and his sons, the sons and daughters of the newest members of our society will come to the calling and make the sacrifices. What makes this country work, is not the fact that we ever &quot;worked together&quot; in a unity fashion, because it never happened, but that we can survive and thrive BECAUSE of the diversity of thought and peoples. There are differences amongst all Americans, you, me, and everybody else, and we thrive on it. This country is not being pulled apart nor is it falling apart. I love what Gerald Ney's said and I want to re-emphasis it here:<br><br>
&quot;What needs to be remembered is that what is unique about our country is that it wasn't founded upon a nationality, race or creed; but upon the acceptance of the basic governing principles embodied in the Constitution or the Declaration of Independence.&quot; Truely Impressive! I know of not one politician that I have any faith in, but this I truely believe.<br><br>
Now, this is me, the perpetual pessimist, speaking. I have faith in the design of our government. I have faith in the statement of Gerald's written above. I have even more faith in the groups of people of which we speak. I have faith in the Lien's and the Patti's(my daughter)of this country. I have no fears that they will not take this country to greater heights.<br><br>
Now, politicians are another thing.  Let's you and I get together and.............<br><br>
The issue of language was taken out of context, but I realize that in California, this is a long standing topic of heated debate that I have no desire to participate in.  I know it is not an issue here, but I cannot, for the life of me, remember how it ever was dealt with here. So I will stay out of this one, because, to tell you the truth, I don't care.<br><br>
So, on that note, take care, Doc and everyone else. As the perpetual pessimist, I have absolutely no faith that this site will endure much longer. Should that be so, I want you to know, it was fun. Thanks to those who said good words on my writings.
<p><code>-- docdel@maui.net  (Doc Del) </code><p>


